ical effects could serve as a\npowerful theoretical tool for future study of optoelectronic and spintronics\ndevices consisting of van der Waals 2D magnets.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 1 Jun 2021 20:09:10 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 30 Jan 2022 01:43:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-02-01"}
