ely long orbital periods quite well. We also found that such UCXBs\ncan be identified by their locations in the mass-transfer rate versus the\norbital period diagram.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 2 Jun 2021 08:07:09 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 13 Jul 2021 11:20:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-08-09"}
